oai_dc:dc.dc:title: ALTERNATIVES TO BEACH STABILIZATION: CAMBRILS COAST CASE STUDY (SPAIN)
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Lupon, Nuria
Vidaor, Alfonso
Galofre, Jordi
Escartin, F. Javier
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: beach stabalization
Cambrils Coast
case study
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A study of alternatives including a shoreline evolution numerical modelization has been carried out in order to both diagnose the erosion problem at the beaches located between Cambrils Harbour and Pixerota delta (Tarragona, Spain) and select nourishment alternatives.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 25 (1996): Proceedings of 25th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Orlando, Florida, 1996.
